---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/Global.css";
---

<DocLayout title="Installation">
    <section id="installation">
        <h1 class="docs-title">Installation</h1>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="achieve">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">What You’ll Achieve</h2>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                If you are searching for an <span class="docs-para-highlight"
                    >AstroAnimate installation guide</span
                > , this page solves the exact setup task: install AstroAnimate correctly,
                confirm compatibility, and run a working first import in your Astro
                app.
            </p>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">By the end of this page, you will:</p>
            <ul class="docs-list">
                <li>Install AstroAnimate using the correct package name</li>
                <li>
                    Verify Astro version compatibility before implementation
                </li>
                <li>Add a component import in a real `.astro` page</li>
                <li>Run checks to validate install quality before shipping</li>
                <li>Fix common install-time errors quickly</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="prerequisites">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Prerequisites / Requirements</h2>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                Before installing, confirm the following:
            </p>
            <ul class="docs-list">
                <li>You already have an Astro project.</li>
                <li>
                    Your project uses a compatible Astro version (` <span
                        class="component">^4.0.0 || ^5.0.0</span
                    >`).
                </li>
                <li>You can run npm commands from your project root.</li>
                <li>
                    You have write access to '<span class="component"
                        >package.json</span
                    >' and lockfile updates.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="step-by-step">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Step-by-Step Guide</h2>

            <div class="steps-container">
                <!-- STEP 1 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="step-1">
                    <h3 class="step-title">Step 1: Install the package</h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        Run this command from your Astro project root:
                    </p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block">
                        <div class="code-header">
                            <span>bash</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-wrapper">
                            <pre><code><span class="keyword">npm</span> install <span class="string">@astroanimate/core</span></code></pre>
                            <button
                                class="copy-btn-icon"
                                aria-label="Copy code"
                            >
                                <svg
                                    width="24"
                                    height="24"
                                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                                    fill="none"
                                    stroke="currentColor"
                                    stroke-width="2"
                                    stroke-linecap="round"
                                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                                    ><rect
                                        x="9"
                                        y="9"
                                        width="13"
                                        height="13"
                                        rx="2"
                                        ry="2"></rect><path
                                        d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"
                                    ></path></svg
                                >
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        This installs the official AstroAnimate package.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- STEP 2 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="step-2">
                    <h3 class="step-title">
                        Step 2: Import your first component
                    </h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        Use a direct component import for a clear first
                        validation:
                    </p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block">
                        <pre><code><span class="comment">---</span>
<span class="component">import</span> <span>FadeIn</span> <span class="component">from</span> <span class="string">"@astroanimate/core/FadeIn"</span>;
<span class="comment">---</span>

&lt;<span class="brand">main</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="brand">FadeIn</span> <span class="string">enhance</span> <span class="string">direction</span>=<span class="component">"up"</span> <span class="string">distance</span>={<span class="number">{20}</span>} <span class="string">once</span>&gt;
    &lt;<span class="brand">h1</span>&gt;AstroAnimate is installed&lt;/<span class="brand">h1</span>&gt;
  &lt;/<span class="brand">FadeIn</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="brand">main</span>&gt;</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- STEP 3 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="step-3">
                    <h3 class="step-title">
                        Step 3: Optional: import from root exports
                    </h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        AstroAnimate also exposes root exports. If your team
                        prefers grouped imports:
                    </p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block">
                        <pre><code style="color: #F9FAFB;">---
import &#123; FadeIn, SlideIn, TextRotate &#125; from "@astroanimate/core";
---</code></pre>
                    </div>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        Use this style when you want centralized imports in
                        shared UI files.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- STEP 4 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="step-4">
                    <h3 class="step-title">
                        Step 4: Run install quality checks
                    </h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        After installation, run these checks:
                    </p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block">
                        <div class="code-wrapper">
                            <pre><code>npm run build
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
npm run test</code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">Why this matters:</p>
                    <ul class="docs-list">
                        <li>Build confirms bundling integrity.</li>
                        <li>
                            Typecheck catches integration and TS issues early.
                        </li>
                        <li>Lint keeps implementation consistent.</li>
                        <li>Tests reduce regression risk before release.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="docs-callout">
                        Expected result: all checks pass before you proceed to
                        larger adoption in your app.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- STEP 5 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="step-5">
                    <h3 class="step-title">
                        Step 5: Verify in development mode
                    </h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        Run your local dev server and open your page:
                    </p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block dark-bg">
                        <div class="code-wrapper">
                            <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">Validation checklist:</p>
                    <ul class="docs-list">
                        <li>
                            The page renders with no module resolution errors.
                        </li>
                        <li>Imported component appears correctly.</li>
                        <li>
                            If `<span class="string">enhance</span>` is used,
                            behavior is visible in browser (unless
                            reduced-motion preferences suppress animations).
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="troubleshooting">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Notes</h2>

            <ul class="docs-list">
                <li>
                    AstroAnimate is an Astro-native component library; use it
                    inside <span class="string">.astro</span> workflows.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Use the exact package name <span class="string"
                        >@astroanimate/core</span
                    >.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Keep import paths consistent across your codebase (subpath
                    or root-export style).
                </li>
                <li>
                    Some behavior is enhancement-based. If expected interaction
                    is not visible, confirm component props and reduced-motion
                    settings.
                </li>
                <li>
                    For production rollout, run quality checks in CI, not only
                    locally.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="related-resources">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Related Resources</h2>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">Use these internal docs to continue:</p>
            <ul class="docs-list docs-list-links">
                <li>
                    → [Read AstroAnimate
                    Introduction](https://www.notion.so/docs/introduction/)
                </li>
                <li>
                    → [Continue to Quick
                    Start](https://www.notion.so/docs/quick-start/)
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                Suggested next step: complete <span class="docs-para-highlight"
                    >Quick Start
                </span> after this page so your team standardizes first-use patterns.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="faq">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">FAQ (Developer Questions)</h2>
            <div class="faq-container">
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Is AstroAnimate only for Astro? <svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Yes. It is fully built for the Astro ecosystem.
                    </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >How do I install AstroAnimate in Astro? <svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Run: <span class="keyword"
                            >npm install @astroanimate/core</span
                        >. Then import a component in an .astro file and run
                        your app.
                    </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Which Astro versions are supported by AstroAnimate?<svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        AstroAnimate supports Astro ^4.0.0 || ^5.0.0.
                    </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Should I use subpath imports or root imports?<svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Both are supported. Use subpath imports (for example
                        @astroanimate/core/FadeIn) for explicit per-component
                        usage, or root imports (@astroanimate/core) for grouped
                        style conventions.
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Why does my component render but not animate as
                        expected?<svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        <p class="docs-paragraph">Common causes:</p>
                        <ul class="docs-list">
                            <li>
                                Enhancement-based behavior not enabled (when
                                required by component usage)
                            </li>
                            <li>Reduced-motion OS/browser setting active</li>
                            <li>
                                Incorrect props or test condition (for example,
                                scroll-trigger behavior not yet in viewport)
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="docs-paragraph">
                            Start by validating one known working example, then
                            scale.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </details>

                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Can I ship AstroAnimate to production immediately after
                        install?<svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Yes, if your use case matches current components and
                        your quality checks pass. Recommended flow: install →
                        first render → run checks → QA in target
                        browsers/devices → deploy.
                    </div>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-footer-nav" style="justify-content: space-between;">
            <a href="/docs" class="prev-link">
                <span class="label">PREVIOUS</span>
                <span class="title">
                    <svg
                        width="18"
                        height="18"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        style="transform: rotate(180deg);"
                        ><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line><polyline
                            points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline></svg
                    >
                    Introduction
                </span>
            </a>
            <a href="/docs/quick-start" class="next-link">
                <span class="label">NEXT</span>
                <span class="title">
                    Quick Start
                    <svg
                        width="18"
                        height="18"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        ><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line><polyline
                            points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline></svg
                    >
                </span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <Fragment slot="toc">
        <div class="toc-header">IN THIS PAGE</div>
        <nav class="toc-nav">
            <a href="#achieve" class="active">What You'll Achieve</a>
            <a href="#prerequisites">Prerequisites</a>
            <a href="#step-by-step">Step-by-Step Guide</a>
            <a href="#step-1" class="toc-sub">Step 1: Install the package</a>
            <a href="#step-2" class="toc-sub"
                >Step 2: Import your first component</a
            >
            <a href="#step-3" class="toc-sub">Step 3: Optional: root imports</a>
            <a href="#step-4" class="toc-sub"
                >Step 4: Run install quality checks</a
            >
            <a href="#step-5" class="toc-sub"
                >Step 5: Verify in development mode</a
            >
            <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
            <a href="#related-resources">Related Resources</a>
        </nav>
    </Fragment>
</DocLayout>
